## 5. Prediction:

\(a\) Obtain estimates of the random slope by predicting the random effect U1i for each subject and adding these to the fixed effect β1.

```{r}
# fixed slope
b1 <- fixef(parsimonious_model)["time"]

# random effects
r <- ranef(parsimonious_model)

U1 <- r$id$time

# combine
b1_EB <- b1 + U1

# data frame
slope_estimates <- data.frame(
  id = rownames(r$id),
  random_effect = U1,
  individual_slope = b1_EB)

head(slope_estimates)


```

\(b\) Obtain estimates of the random intercept by predicting the random effect U0i for each subject and adding these to the fixed effect β0.

```{r}
# fixed intercept
b0 <- fixef(parsimonious_model)["(Intercept)"]

# random effects
r <- ranef(parsimonious_model)

U0 <- r$id$`(Intercept)`

# combine
b0_EB <- b0 + U0

# data frame
intercept_estimates <- data.frame(
  id = rownames(r$id),
  random_effect = U0,
  individual_intercept = b0_EB)

head(intercept_estimates)

```

